h3 Toolbar Types
p Three toolbar variations are available: <strong>Blank</strong>, <strong>Default</strong> and <strong>Primary</strong>.
p The <strong>Primary toolbar</strong> is most common, and is used in order to draw attention to important inputs/filter functions (etc.).
p
  | The <strong>Default</strong> toolbar is for use-cases where the toolbar offers less-important or fully-optional functions.
    A secondary toolbar, for instance, should always be in the 'Default' style.
p
  | The <strong>Blank</strong> toolbar can be used in rare cases where toolbar behaviour (horizontal grouping of buttons/inputs) is desired,
   but not the visual separation/attention that comes with the toolbar background. This also can achieve the effect of 'floating' toolbar inputs.

